                            <comment id="14051870" author="zariel" created="Thu, 3 Jul 2014 20:13:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to work around these issues with build flags and other means. For instance we can define our own io.ByteWriter interface which will suffice to fix this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although for instance io.ByteWriter is part of go1 so I guess that should be a minimum requirement?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14051920" author="jensg" created="Thu, 3 Jul 2014 21:17:54 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although for instance io.ByteWriter is part of go1 ...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is part of Go 1.1 to be &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/golang/+bug/1058592&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;precise&lt;/a&gt; (pun intended). See &lt;a href=&quot;http://golang.org/doc/go1.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://golang.org/doc/go1.1&lt;/a&gt;, section &quot;Minor changes to the library&quot;. I just checked this a few minutes ago  &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. Jake made me aware of the fact, that 12.04 has only Go 1.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14334353" author="jfarrell" created="Tue, 24 Feb 2015 03:42:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test tools like vet and cover moved from code.google to golang.org in 1.4, do we want to make that the default minimum version? Can mimic what the ubuntu package sets up as default paths on install with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;curl -sSL https:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.4.1.linux-amd64.tar.gz | tar -C /usr/lib/ -xz &amp;amp;&amp;amp; \
&lt;/span&gt;    mkdir -p /usr/share/go

export GOROOT=/usr/lib/go
export GOPATH=/usr/share/go
export PATH=${GOROOT}/bin:${GOPATH}/bin:$PATH
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14337251" author="jensg" created="Wed, 25 Feb 2015 21:32:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I completely forgot about this one. Thanks for the reminder.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14366346" author="jensg" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2015 00:01:43 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test tools like vet and cover moved from code.google to golang.org in 1.4, do we want to make that the default minimum version?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I set it to 1.3 in the patch, worked for me (openSUSE is still at 1.3.3). Had no bad experiences so far. Did you experience any specific problems that would require 1.4?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14366359" author="jfarrell" created="Wed, 18 Mar 2015 00:10:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would like to stay with the latest version for this if possible, the issues I ran into when I initially tested with 1.2/1.3 at the time pointing to code.google.com vs 1.4 pointing to golang.org, i&apos;ve switched to just using the latest go version and have not tested the older versions since&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
